```

### How to get the `&lt;moduleInfoSource&gt;` content?

- go to the folder with the required (dependency) .jar file
- If you use Intellij IDEA, in project view, there&#39;s a section named `External Libraries`. Double-click on the entry, right click on the `.jar`, open in -&gt; Explorer.
- open command prompt in that folder
- `jdeps -generate-module-info . {jar_file_name}.jar`
- Make sure the PATH environment variable is correct
- open the generated `module-info.java` file with a text editor and copy the content
- paste to the `&lt;moduleInfoSource&gt;` section

## Create runtime image (with jlink, in the backend)

- please change the `&lt;modules&gt;`, `&lt;launcher&gt;`sections according to your project information.
- If your module is non-modular, it is important that the main class does not  extend `javafx.Application` directly. We can create a launcher class which looks like this (reference pending):

&gt; launcher class
```java
public class Launcher {  
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
        HelloApplication.main(args);  
    }  
}
```

&gt; pom.xml
```xml
&lt;execution&gt;
	&lt;id&gt;create-runtime-image&lt;/id&gt;
	&lt;phase&gt;package&lt;/phase&gt;
	&lt;goals&gt;
		&lt;goal&gt;create-runtime-image&lt;/goal&gt;
	&lt;/goals&gt;
	&lt;configuration&gt;
		&lt;jarInclusionPolicy&gt;APP_WITH_DEPENDENCIES&lt;/jarInclusionPolicy&gt;
		&lt;modulePath&gt;
			&lt;path&gt;${project.build.directory}/${project.artifactId}-${project.version}.${project.packaging}&lt;/path&gt;
			&lt;path&gt;${project.build.directory}/dependency&lt;/path&gt;
		&lt;/modulePath&gt;
		&lt;modules&gt;
			&lt;module&gt;com.example.soone&lt;/module&gt;
		&lt;/modules&gt;
		&lt;launcher&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;hello&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;module&gt;com.example.soone/com.example.soone.Launcher&lt;/module&gt;
		&lt;/launcher&gt;
		&lt;outputDirectory&gt;
			${project.build.directory}/jlink-image
		&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;
	&lt;/configuration&gt;
&lt;/execution&gt;
```

